text.tspan: Monthly surface temperature anomalies by year, World
The deviation of a specific month's average surface temperature from the 1991–2020 mean, in degrees Celsius.
Data source: Contains modified Copernicus Climate Change Service information (2019)
Note: The numbers 1 to 12 on the horizontal axis represent the months of the year, from 1 for January to 12 for December. For clarity,
the year 2020 and subsequent years are highlighted in red.
